```mermaid
%% Content Management and Update Workflows
sequenceDiagram
    participant Editor as Content Editor
    participant CMS as Content Management System
    participant Review as Review Process
    participant API as FAQ API
    participant Cache as Cache System
    participant User as End User
    
    %% Content Creation Workflow
    Editor->>CMS: Create New FAQ
    CMS->>CMS: Generate FAQ ID
    CMS->>Editor: Provide FAQ Form
    Editor->>CMS: Submit FAQ Content
    CMS->>CMS: Validate Content Format
    CMS->>Review: Send for Review
    
    %% Review Process
    Review->>Review: Editorial Review
    Review->>Review: Technical Accuracy Check
    Review->>Review: SEO Optimization
    alt Content Approved
        Review->>CMS: Approve FAQ
        CMS->>API: Publish FAQ
        API->>Cache: Update FAQ Cache
        Cache->>User: New FAQ Available
    else Content Needs Changes
        Review->>Editor: Request Revisions
        Editor->>CMS: Submit Revised Content
        CMS->>Review: Re-submit for Review
    end
    
    %% Content Update Workflow
    Editor->>CMS: Request FAQ Update
    CMS->>Editor: Load Existing Content
    Editor->>CMS: Submit Updated Content
    CMS->>CMS: Track Version History
    CMS->>Review: Send Updates for Review
    
    Review->>Review: Compare Changes
    Review->>Review: Validate Updates
    alt Updates Approved
        Review->>CMS: Approve Updates
        CMS->>API: Deploy Updated FAQ
        API->>Cache: Invalidate Old Cache
        Cache->>User: Updated FAQ Available
        CMS->>CMS: Archive Old Version
    else Updates Rejected
        Review->>Editor: Request Further Changes
    end
    
    %% User Feedback Integration
    User->>API: Submit FAQ Feedback
    API->>CMS: Log Feedback
    CMS->>CMS: Analyze Feedback Trends
    CMS->>Editor: Flag FAQs Needing Updates
    Editor->>CMS: Review Flagged Content
    
    %% Automated Content Maintenance
    CMS->>CMS: Run Daily Content Audit
    CMS->>CMS: Check for Outdated Information
    CMS->>CMS: Validate External Links
    CMS->>Editor: Generate Maintenance Report
    Editor->>CMS: Address Maintenance Issues
    
    %% Content Performance Tracking
    API->>CMS: Send Usage Analytics
    CMS->>CMS: Analyze FAQ Performance
    CMS->>Editor: Provide Performance Reports
    Editor->>CMS: Optimize Low-Performing FAQs
